mchorse.mappet.api.scripts.user

Interface IScriptEntity


  • public interface IScriptEntity
    Entity interface. This interface represents an entity, it could be a player, NPC, or any other entity.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.String entityId()
      Get entity's resource location ID, like "minecraft:pig" or "minecraft:zombie"
      float hp()
      Get health points of this entity (20 is the max default for players)
      boolean isPlayer()
      Check whether this entity is a player
      boolean isSneaking()
      Is this entity is sneaking
      boolean isSprinting()
      Is this entity is sprinting
      void kill()
      Kill this entity from the server by inflicting lots of damage (similar to /kill command)
      IScriptItemStack mainItem()
      Get item held in main hand
      ScriptVector motion()
      Get entity's motion
      void motion(double x, double y, double z)
      Set entity's motion
      IScriptItemStack offItem()
      Get item held in off hand
      ScriptVector position()
      Get entity's position
      void position(double x, double y, double z)
      Set entity's position (teleport)
      void remove()
      Remove this entity from the server without any dead effects
      IMappetStates states()
      Get states of this entity (if it has some, only players have states)
      java.lang.String uniqueId()
      Get unique ID of this entity, which can be used, if needed, in commands as a target selector
